    "sa_faq_aHnqeL": {
      "type": "sa-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "tab_xxkXC7": {
          "type": "tab",
          "settings": {
            "label": "Products Features"
          }
        },
        "qa_WhXaje": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "1",
            "question": "<p>What are the key upgrades of the Yarbo Lawn Mower Pro compared to the standard Yarbo Lawn Mower?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yarbo Lawn Mower Pro features dual 300W motors delivering 2500W peak power—double the standard 150W motors. It includes optional straight blades for finer cuts and an enhanced cutting height range down to 0.8 inches (2 cm). These upgrades make it ideal for both residential properties up to 6 acres and commercial applications like golf courses and resorts. It excels with cool and warm-season grasses, as well as wet, thick, and overgrown lawns.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_eizRdy": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "1",
            "question": "<p>Is Yarbo Lawn Mower Pro the best for large lawns?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Absolutely. Yarbo Lawn Mower navigates slopes up to 35° (70%) and adapts to complex terrain, including ditches, trees, and ponds. The tracked drive system and powerful motors deliver reliable performance on uneven, rugged lawns—ensuring Yarbo Lawn Mower maintains consistent cutting quality even on challenging properties.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_hBeDq7": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "1",
            "question": "<p>What is the cutting height range and why can it cut grass lower?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>The cutting height adjusts from 0.8 to 4.0 inches (2–10 cm). The ability to cut lower comes from reinforced blades that press deeper into dense grass. With dual 300W motors, Yarbo Lawn Mower Pro delivers the power needed to handle thick, established turf at lower heights—a feature typically required for commercial-grade applications and warm-season grasses.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_PRPhYx": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "1",
            "question": "<p>What types of grass can the Yarbo Lawn Mower Pro handle?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yarbo Lawn Mower Pro handles all-season grasses with exceptional performance on challenging warm-season varieties. It efficiently tackles Zoysia, Buffalo Grass, St. Augustine, Bermuda, and Kikuyu—grasses known for being dense, tough, and difficult to mow. The 300W motors and straight blade option ensure clean cuts even in wet, thick, or overgrown conditions.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_bxjMJ9": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "1",
            "question": "<p>What blade options come with the Yarbo Lawn Mower Pro?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Two-blade systems are included: dual cutting discs with 5 reinforced razor blades each (standard), and optional straight blades made from SK85 high-carbon steel. The straight blades deliver finer mulching, greater durability, and smoother operation—ideal for users seeking the best for large lawn maintenance with minimal blade replacements.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_kXeJ4U": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "1",
            "question": "<p>Will the Yarbo Lawn Mower Pro face clogging issues?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>No. The straight blades virtually eliminate clogging, and the redesigned disc system significantly reduces it. Blades rotate outward to eject cut grass efficiently, and the simplified deck structure prevents buildup. This automatic lawn mower powers through dense grass and heavy debris without stalling—ensuring uninterrupted autonomous operation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "tab_wAwarR": {
          "type": "tab",
          "settings": {
            "label": "Support & Care"
          }
        },
        "qa_mYx8Dx": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>What maintenance is needed for blades, tracks, and general upkeep?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Minimal upkeep keeps the Yarbo Lawn Mower Pro performing optimally. Replace blades every 3 months with heavy use (tool-free replacement). Clean and lubricate tracks regularly, checking tension periodically. Monthly maintenance: clean cameras and sensors, wipe exterior housing, update firmware via the Yarbo app. During storage, charge the battery for 15 minutes every 3 months to prevent degradation. A seasonal inspection is recommended.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_U64Upc": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>I'm having trouble with setup—what should I do?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Follow the step-by-step guide in the Yarbo App or included user manual. For additional help, visit wiki.yarbo.com, join our Discord Forum, or connect with users in our Official Facebook Group. Reach 24/7 support at 1 (631) 818-1850, email <a href=\"mailto:support@yarbo.com\">support@yarbo.com</a>, or submit a ticket through the Yarbo App.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_67edJa": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>What is Yarbo’s return policy?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yarbo offers a <strong>30-day return policy</strong> for eligible products.To qualify for a return:</p><ul><li> The product must be in <strong>original packaging</strong></li><li> All accessories and documentation must be included </li><li> The item must be in <strong>resalable condition</strong></li></ul><p>Return shipping fees and packaging costs may be deducted if applicable.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_7BLQFi": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>What warranty does Yarbo offer?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yarbo products include a <strong>2-year limited warranty</strong>.You can also choose an <strong>optional 3-year extended warranty</strong>, providing up to <strong>5 years of total coverage</strong> (available in select regions).</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_paWyAp": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>Can I cancel my order after placing it?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yes—orders can be canceled before shipment.<br/>If the order has already shipped, it will be treated as a return and subject to the return policy.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_je46gE": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>What if my delivery is delayed?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>While Yarbo aims for fast delivery, delays may occur due to:</p><ul><li> Weather conditions </li><li> Carrier issues </li><li> High seasonal demand </li></ul><p>Yarbo will keep you updated with tracking and support assistance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_47qTrJ": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>How can I contact Yarbo support?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>You can reach Yarbo through:</p><ul><li> Email: <strong>support@yarbo.com</strong></li><li> Phone: <strong>+1 (631) 818-1850</strong></li><li> Yarbo App support system </li></ul><p>Support is available <strong>24/7</strong>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_9BTWgU": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>How long does Yarbo shipping take?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yarbo orders typically ship within <strong>3–8 business days</strong> for in-stock products in the United States.<br/> For <strong>pre-order items</strong>, delivery timelines are shown on the product page.For <strong>Canada and Europe</strong>:</p><ul><li> Core & Modules: 3–8 business days </li><li> Accessories: 10–15 business days </li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
